Role: You are an expert Python developer specializing in Flask web applications and precise PDF manipulation (using PyMuPDF / fitz or pypdf).
Context: I have an existing Flask application with various tools. I need to add a new tool that processes Amazon shipping label PDFs uploaded by users.
The Problem: Users upload multiple A4-sized PDF files containing Amazon shipping labels. Currently, each page is divided vertically into two halves:
Left Half: Contains up to 2 shipping labels (stacked vertically).
Right Half: Contains the corresponding tax invoices (stacked vertically).
(Note: Sometimes an input page might only have 1 label on the left and 1 invoice on the right, leaving the bottom blank. The geometric split remains exactly the same).
The Goal: I want to discard all invoices (the right halves) to save paper. I need to extract only the left halves (the shipping labels) from all uploaded PDFs, and pack them tightly onto new A4 pages. By placing the extracted left half of Page 1 onto the left side of a new A4 page, and the extracted left half of Page 2 onto the right side of that same new A4 page, the final output will beautifully fit 4 shipping labels per physical A4 sheet.
Technical Requirements:
Multiple Uploads: The Flask route must accept multiple PDF file uploads simultaneously from a form (request.files.getlist).
Combine & Process: Merge all uploaded PDFs in the order they were uploaded to process them as a single document flow.
Dimension Calculation (A4 Size):
Standard A4 dimensions in points: width = 595.28, height = 841.89.
Original Left Half Box: (0, 0, 297.64, 841.89)
Transformation Logic (The "Cut and Paste"):
Iterate through every page of the combined input PDFs.
Extract/crop the left half of each page.
Create a new blank A4 PDF document.
Take the first extracted left half and place it on the left half (0, 0, 297.64, 841.89) of the new Page 1.
Take the second extracted left half and place it on the right half (297.64, 0, 595.28, 841.89) of the new Page 1.
Continue this process, creating a new page for every 2 extracted halves.
Handle odd numbers of total pages gracefully (the final output page will just have a left half filled and the right half blank).
Output: Save the final combined and reformatted PDF to an in-memory buffer (io.BytesIO) and return it as a downloadable file to the user using Flask's send_file with a proper filename like optimized_shipping_labels.pdf.
